  "900": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n📖 QWEN IMAGE STORY — 10 SCENE WORKFLOW\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nThis workflow generates a 10-scene visual story\nwith CONSISTENT CHARACTER across all scenes.\n\n🔹 HOW IT WORKS:\n1. Upload your reference images into the\n   Multi Image Loader node (node 78)\n2. Assign roles: Main Character, Background, Object\n3. Write scene prompts referencing image 1/2/3\n4. Hit Queue Prompt — all 10 scenes generate\n\n🔹 IMAGE ROUTING:\n• image1 = Your character (SAME for ALL scenes)\n• image2 = Background ref (Scene 1) or\n           Previous scene output (Scenes 2-10)\n• image3 = Object/prop reference\n\n🔹 KEY IMPROVEMENT:\nEvery scene receives the ORIGINAL character\nreference — no more drift from chaining!\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "📖 WORKFLOW OVERVIEW"
    }
  },

  "901": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n🖼️ MULTI IMAGE LOADER — HOW TO USE\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. Click 'Upload Images' to add reference photos\n2. The FIRST image auto-assigns to 'Main Character'\n3. Subsequent images default to 'Background'\n4. Use the dropdown on each thumbnail to change role:\n   🟡 Gold border   = Main Character\n   🟢 Green border  = Background\n   🟠 Orange border = Object\n\n⚠️ RULES:\n• Only ONE image can be Main Character\n• If you assign a second as Main Character,\n  the previous one switches to Background\n• If no image is assigned to a role,\n  a blank 512x512 image is output for that port\n\n🔌 OUTPUT PORTS:\n  Port 0: main_character (IMAGE)\n  Port 1: background    (IMAGE)\n  Port 2: objects        (IMAGE)\n  Port 3: prompt_prefix  (STRING)\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "🖼️ IMAGE LOADER GUIDE"
    }
  },

  "902": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n💬 PROMPT MODE — CONTROLLING PREFIX\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nThe 'prompt_mode' dropdown controls the\nauto-generated text prepended to your prompts:\n\n▸ 'minimal' (DEFAULT — recommended)\n  Adds: \"same character as image 1,\n  background from image 2, props from image 3.\"\n  Light touch, works for most scenes.\n\n▸ 'off'\n  No prefix added. Images still route correctly.\n  Use when the prefix hurts output quality.\n  You can manually write \"image 1\" references.\n\n▸ 'detailed'\n  Full instructional paragraph enforcing\n  consistency. Use when character is drifting.\n\n▸ 'custom'\n  Uses your text from the 'custom_prefix' field.\n  Write your own tested prefix template.\n\n💡 TIP: If a scene looks worse with the prefix,\nswitch to 'off' for that run. The Qwen model\nstill uses the images as visual conditioning\neven without text references.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "💬 PROMPT MODE GUIDE"
    }
  },

  "903": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n⚙️ SHARED MODEL CONFIGURATION\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nThese nodes are shared across ALL 10 scenes:\n\n• UNETLoader (433:37)\n  Model: qwen_image_edit_2509_fp8_e4m3fn\n\n• CLIPLoader (433:38)\n  CLIP: qwen_2.5_vl_7b_fp8_scaled\n  Type: qwen_image\n\n• VAELoader (433:39)\n  VAE: qwen_image_vae\n\n• LoRA Lightning (433:89)\n  4-step lightning for fast generation\n\n• ModelSamplingAuraFlow (433:66)\n  Shift: 3\n\n• CFGNorm (433:75)\n  Strength: 1\n\n⚠️ Do NOT disconnect these nodes!\nAll 10 scenes depend on them.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "⚙️ MODEL CONFIG"
    }
  },

  "904": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n🔗 SCENE CHAIN ARCHITECTURE\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nScene 1:\n  image1 ← Main Character (node 700)\n  image2 ← Background ref (node 701)\n  image3 ← Object ref (node 702)\n  VAE encode ← Main Character (scaled)\n\nScenes 2-10:\n  image1 ← Main Character (SAME, node 700)\n  image2 ← Previous scene OUTPUT (continuity)\n  image3 ← Object ref (node 702)\n  VAE encode ← Previous scene output (scaled)\n\n📐 Shared Scale Nodes:\n  700 = Scale Main Character to 2K\n  701 = Scale Background to 2K\n  702 = Scale Objects to 2K\n\nThis means:\n✅ Character stays consistent (original ref)\n✅ Scene continuity maintained (prev output)\n✅ Objects persist across scenes\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "🔗 SCENE CHAIN"
    }
  },

  "905": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n✏️ HOW TO WRITE SCENE PROMPTS\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nEach scene has a [EDIT] prompt node.\nWrite your scene description there.\n\n🔹 REFERENCE IMAGES BY NUMBER:\n\"The character from image 1 stands in\nthe forest from image 2, holding the\nsword from image 3.\"\n\n🔹 KEEP IT CONSISTENT:\nAlways describe the character the same way:\n\"same face, same outfit, same hair\"\n\n🔹 GOOD PROMPT EXAMPLE:\n\"Scene 3: The same character from image 1\ndiscovers glowing ancient ruins, standing\nin awe before the stone carvings. Magical\nlight illuminates their face. Same outfit.\nCinematic wide shot, detailed background.\"\n\n🔹 BAD PROMPT (too vague):\n\"A person in some ruins\"\n(No image reference, no consistency cues)\n\n🔹 SEEDS:\nEach scene has a unique seed (42001-42010).\nChange seeds to explore variations.\nLock a seed when you like the result.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "✏️ PROMPT WRITING TIPS"
    }
  },

  "906": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n💾 OUTPUT FILES\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nGenerated images are saved as:\n  Story_Scene_01_00001.png\n  Story_Scene_02_00001.png\n  ...\n  Story_Scene_10_00001.png\n\nThey appear in your ComfyUI output folder.\n\n📐 Resolution: 2048 × 1152 (2K cinematic)\n\n🎬 To make a video from the scenes:\n  ffmpeg -framerate 1 -i Story_Scene_%02d_00001.png \\\n    -c:v libx264 -pix_fmt yuv420p story.mp4\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "💾 OUTPUT FILES"
    }
  },

  "907": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n🔧 TROUBLESHOOTING\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\n❌ 'Character looks different each scene'\n→ Make sure image1 on EVERY scene's Positive\n  encoder points to node 700 (character ref)\n→ Add \"same face, same outfit\" to prompts\n→ Try 'detailed' prompt mode\n\n❌ 'Background/objects not showing up'\n→ Check that you uploaded images and assigned\n  them the correct role in the Multi Image Loader\n→ Verify the dropdown shows Background/Object\n→ Reference them in your prompt as image 2 / 3\n\n❌ 'Prompt prefix makes output worse'\n→ Switch prompt_mode to 'off'\n→ Images still route correctly without prefix\n→ Write your own references manually\n→ Or try 'custom' mode with your own wording\n\n❌ 'Blank/black images coming out'\n→ A role with no uploaded image outputs blank\n→ Upload at least a Main Character image\n→ Background and Object are optional\n\n❌ 'Node not found / red nodes'\n→ Make sure mult_image is installed in\n  ComfyUI custom_nodes/ directory\n→ Restart ComfyUI after installing\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "🔧 TROUBLESHOOTING"
    }
  },

  "908": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "═══════════════════════════════════════════\n📋 PER-SCENE QUICK REFERENCE\n═══════════════════════════════════════════\n\nEach scene block contains these nodes:\n\n1️⃣ [EDIT] Scene N Prompt\n   → Write your scene description here\n   → Reference image 1, 2, 3 as needed\n\n2️⃣ Image Scale 2K - Scene N\n   → Scales previous scene output to 2K\n   → Scene 1 scales the character reference\n\n3️⃣ VAE Encode Tiled - Scene N\n   → Encodes the scaled image to latent space\n\n4️⃣ Positive - Scene N\n   → Text + image conditioning\n   → image1 = character, image2 = context,\n     image3 = objects\n\n5️⃣ Negative - Scene N\n   → Empty prompt + character image only\n   → Keeps unconditional guidance anchored\n\n6️⃣ KSampler - Scene N\n   → Generates the scene (4 steps, euler)\n   → Unique seed per scene\n\n7️⃣ VAE Decode Tiled - Scene N\n   → Decodes latent back to image\n\n8️⃣ Save Image - Scene N\n   → Saves as Story_Scene_NN_XXXXX.png\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════"
    },
    "class_type": "Note",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "📋 PER-SCENE REFERENCE"
    }
  }
}